OL,3,CSister of Sabina Nessa welcomes plans
OL,4,Cto punish criminals who avoid
OL,5,Csentencing
OL,7,FUnder the new legislation, judges will
OL,8,Fbe given the power to sentence
OL,9,Foffenders for up to two more years in
OL,10,Fprison.
OL,12,FFor those who already face lengthy
OL,13,Fimprisonment or whole life orders,
OL,14,Fjudges could also impose a range of
OL,15,Fprison punishments on offenders such
OL,16,Fas confinement to their cells and
OL,17,Fbeing stripped of privileges such as
OL,18,Fextra gym time.
